      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHE'S RELOADED (3) clocked a useful 16.78 when placed over 300m at this track last start in a Grade 5. Smart effort latest and looks a key chance again here. ASTON MONSOON (1) was sent out long odds last time but rocketed out of the boxes with a fast early sectional and gave a sight before being swallowed up late, finishing a 2.25 lengths third (22.69) over 400m at Geelong. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Expected to be in this for a long way. MINI MILKY (8) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (22.77) at Geelong behind Eagle Tegan in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Leading chance. SIMPLY PETITE (6) cannot be ruled out.",
